3 (2) The bureau shall report the progress and final results of its feasibility study to the water policy
4 interim committee established in 5-5-231, in accordance with 5-11-210. The committee shall consider the
5 results of the study and make recommendations to the legislature for department suspension or closure of new
6 ground water appropriations from the Fox Hills-Hell Creek aquifer.
7
8 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Transfer. By June 30, 2025, the state treasurer shall transfer $5,000
9 $50,000 from the general fund to the ground water assessment account in 85-2-905.
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Appropriation. There is appropriated $5,000 $50,000 from the general
12 fund to the bureau of mines and geology for the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, for a feasibility study
13 pursuant to subsection (3) of [section 1(1)].
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
16 integral part of Title 85, chapter 2, part 3, and the provisions of Title 85, chapter 2, part 3, apply to [section 1].
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Termination. [This act] terminates June 30, 2027.
